article.headline: Maryland-Baltimore County 56, Hampton 49
article.story: HAMPTON, Va. (AP) -- Chris Pugh had a career-high 21 points and 10 rebounds to lead Maryland-Baltimore County to a 56-49 win over Hampton on Saturday. The Retrievers (1-2) trailed only once in the opening minutes of the first and took a 25-14 lead going into halftime, after forcing 15 turnovers. The Pirates (1-3) were kept to 27.3 percent from the floor for the game, but crept to within a point on a jumper by Rashad West with 8:08 remaining. Maryland-Baltimore County ended a 10-2 run with 3:49 remaining, giving the Retrievers a 46-36 lead. Chris Seaborn added two baskets in the last 1:11 to keep a double-digit lead. Jay Green added 11 points for the Retrievers, who snapped a nine-game road losing streak that extended into last season. West led Hampton with 14 points, and Vincent Simpson added 13.
